28:07.186 --> 28:09.186
Thank you, lauren.

28:14.325 --> 28:15.959
(groans)

28:15.961 --> 28:19.063
(helicopter approaching)

28:19.065 --> 28:20.931
Liv?

28:22.834 --> 28:24.001
(sighs)

28:24.003 --> 28:25.803
That's my ride.

28:25.805 --> 28:27.905
(sighs)

28:28.840 --> 28:31.408
Could you?

28:31.410 --> 28:36.447
(kisses) stay another day.
We could hide out here.

28:36.449 --> 28:38.415
Mm.

28:38.417 --> 28:41.018
I have to go.
I have work.

28:41.020 --> 28:45.155
And you have to go.

28:45.157 --> 28:46.990
You have a world to run.

28:46.992 --> 28:49.259
(chuckles)
(chuckles)

28:51.930 --> 28:53.764
(sighs)

28:57.836 --> 29:00.938
What?

29:00.940 --> 29:02.806
I love you.

29:02.808 --> 29:05.375
Fitz, I really do
have to go--

29:05.377 --> 29:07.478
No, I'm saying...

29:09.814 --> 29:11.181
Your father
has to be stopped.

29:11.183 --> 29:13.984
And I want you to know
before I stop him.

29:13.986 --> 29:15.753
I want you to hear me
when I say that I love you

29:15.755 --> 29:17.888
No matter what happens.

29:17.890 --> 29:19.923
Because I need answers.

29:19.925 --> 29:22.359
I was ordered to shoot down
that plane.

29:22.361 --> 29:23.393
And after
I get those answers...

29:23.395 --> 29:25.262
Do what you have to do.

29:25.264 --> 29:26.463
You're sure?

29:26.465 --> 29:27.898
He's your father.

29:27.900 --> 29:29.900
He's the head of b613.

29:29.902 --> 29:32.770
He knows what
he signed up for.

29:32.772 --> 29:37.074
Do what you have to do.

29:37.076 --> 29:41.178
Because I'm not gonna stop
until I have answers either.

30:06.838 --> 30:09.173
(sighs)

30:09.175 --> 30:12.242
(helicopter blades whirring)

30:25.323 --> 30:28.225
Don't sell the house.

30:28.227 --> 30:30.127
Not yet.

30:42.340 --> 30:44.575
All right, got it.
Thanks, brian.

30:44.577 --> 30:46.443
I'll be in soon.

30:46.445 --> 30:47.845
(beep)

30:51.182 --> 30:53.450
What?

30:53.452 --> 30:55.452
That was my computer guy.
And?

30:55.454 --> 30:58.088
Since we're in bed and this
isn't a business dealing,

30:58.090 --> 30:59.890
I am gonna pretend
we're a normal couple

30:59.892 --> 31:02.326
And not automatically suspect
you and your co-workers

31:02.328 --> 31:04.595
Of committing election fraud...
Again.

31:04.597 --> 31:06.330
What are you
talking about?

31:06.332 --> 31:07.965
My computer guy says

31:07.967 --> 31:10.901
Is a stump speech
and a few donor addresses--

31:10.903 --> 31:13.203
Nothing that would really
help an opposing campaign.

31:13.205 --> 31:15.439
That's weird.
Not really.

31:15.441 --> 31:16.974
Especially when you consider
that there used to be

31:16.976 --> 31:18.976
A lot more on that computer,
but it was wiped clean

31:18.978 --> 31:20.277
The day
before the break-in.

31:20.279 --> 31:23.113
You can't think that...

31:23.115 --> 31:26.083
David, are you accusing me
of faking a burglary,

31:26.085 --> 31:27.517
And then
planting that laptop

31:27.519 --> 31:28.652
In reston's campaign
headquarters?

31:28.654 --> 31:30.654
No, no, I am not.

31:30.656 --> 31:34.591
Ask their girlfriends
first thing in the morning.
Good.

31:34.593 --> 31:36.960
Because I didn't do that,
and neither did liv.

31:36.962 --> 31:38.528
Good.

31:38.530 --> 31:40.631
I'm gonna take a shower
and then go into work,

31:40.633 --> 31:43.934
At which point I will resume
being a professional.

31:43.936 --> 31:46.270
(footsteps depart)

31:49.974 --> 31:51.608
(buttons click)

31:53.244 --> 31:55.078
Josie's little break-in?
It was faked.

31:55.080 --> 31:58.682
Her sister. Or daughter.
Or sister/daughter. Whatever.

31:58.684 --> 31:59.616
Candace!

31:59.618 --> 32:02.519
Candace could've had
one of her campaign workers

32:02.521 --> 32:04.288
Drop it off
at reston's headquarters.

32:04.290 --> 32:05.656
You know what
those places are like--

32:05.658 --> 32:07.224
People are coming
and going all day.

32:07.226 --> 32:09.259
M-m-maybe it was somebody else
from the staff.

32:09.261 --> 32:10.994
Harrison, who discovered
the break-in?

32:10.996 --> 32:12.596
Who jumped the gun
with the press?

32:12.598 --> 32:14.398
Who's been driving this
whole thing from the get-go?

32:14.400 --> 32:15.632
Okay, okay. What do you
want me to do about it?

32:15.634 --> 32:16.667
Talk to the sister.

32:16.669 --> 32:19.670
Yeah. Fine.

32:19.672 --> 32:21.138
(cell phone beeps)

32:21.140 --> 32:22.606
Who was that?

32:24.609 --> 32:26.243
Work.

32:26.245 --> 32:27.411
<i>(fitz) I couldn't be happier</i>
<i>to be back</i>

32:27.413 --> 32:32.849
<i>So that's what the goal</i>
<i>of this trip is--</i>

32:32.851 --> 32:34.584
<i>To hear it straight</i>
<i>from the horse's mouth.</i>

32:34.586 --> 32:35.719
<i>If you'll excuse me,</i>
<i>I've got a stack of pancakes</i>

32:35.721 --> 32:37.254
<i>Waiting for me inside.</i>

32:37.256 --> 32:38.956
(door opens)
(cyrus) that's our boy!

32:38.958 --> 32:41.224
(door closes)
what did I tell ya?
A few days on the road,

32:41.226 --> 32:42.726
Shaking hands
and kissing babies,

32:42.728 --> 32:44.728
And he's acting like
a president again.

32:44.730 --> 32:47.998
If that's why you're here.
Other than arranging for him

32:48.000 --> 32:49.533
To bump into james
in a locker room,

32:49.535 --> 32:50.667
I don't know what else
I can do.

32:50.669 --> 32:52.269
Yeah, I thought of
the locker room, too.

32:52.271 --> 32:53.403
Cyrus!

32:53.405 --> 32:55.138
It's happening tonight
is why I'm here.

32:55.140 --> 32:58.742
Sally's still out of town.
So james is going over

32:58.744 --> 33:00.544
To the naval observatory
for dinner.

33:00.546 --> 33:02.679
There'll be wine, candles,
a guy named lionel

33:02.681 --> 33:04.581
Hiding in a tree
with a telephoto lens.

33:04.583 --> 33:05.716
Are you sure you want
to do this?

33:05.718 --> 33:07.451
This is a marriage
we're talking about.

33:07.453 --> 33:09.987
Sally must suspect
her husband's a big gay slut.

33:09.989 --> 33:12.189
We're just making sure
she knows we know.

33:12.191 --> 33:14.191
Not sally's marriage.

33:14.193 --> 33:17.094
You're worried about james
cheating on <i>me?</i>

33:17.096 --> 33:18.729
That's...
(sighs)

33:18.731 --> 33:23.233
You cannot close it again.
It changes you.

33:23.235 --> 33:29.406
My husband's...
Not your husband, mellie.

33:35.346 --> 33:36.613
I tried to call you last night.
Everything okay?

33:36.615 --> 33:40.183
Yeah, I was just busy.

33:40.185 --> 33:43.020
I told you he'd find a way,
didn't I?

33:45.656 --> 33:46.723
(abby) I thought you said
this would work.

33:46.725 --> 33:48.091
(huck) I thought it would.

33:48.093 --> 33:49.426
What's not working?

33:49.428 --> 33:50.560
We still can't identify

33:50.562 --> 33:54.431
Facial recognition
software?
Nothing.

33:54.433 --> 33:56.066
What happens if
we let the program run longer?

33:56.068 --> 33:58.068
No point. This is the highest
resolution I could get.

33:58.070 --> 33:59.770
Our base image was too flawed.

33:59.772 --> 34:03.373
So we're back to square one.
Liv...

34:03.375 --> 34:06.410
They're here.

34:06.412 --> 34:07.511
This is the game, josie.
This is how it--

34:07.513 --> 34:08.745
This isn't a game!

34:08.747 --> 34:09.813
This is watergate!

34:09.815 --> 34:12.082
Josie.

34:12.084 --> 34:13.617
How is what I did
any different

34:13.619 --> 34:15.519
Than what these people--
the people you wanted to hire--

34:15.521 --> 34:17.187
Do on an hourly basis?

34:17.189 --> 34:18.755
You... Got... Caught.

34:18.757 --> 34:21.691
Can I have a moment
with the congresswoman, please?

34:21.693 --> 34:23.894
(footsteps depart,
door opens)

34:27.231 --> 34:28.465
(door closes)

34:28.467 --> 34:31.435
It's just...
We were gaining ground...

34:31.437 --> 34:33.470
With endorsements
and support at rallies.

34:33.472 --> 34:37.240
If we handle this right,
it's a bump in the road.

34:37.242 --> 34:38.842
And how you handle it
will help show

34:38.844 --> 34:41.478
Your leadership abilities
and define your character.

34:41.480 --> 34:43.513
But you're going to have
to fire candace.

34:43.515 --> 34:44.648
Make an example of her.

34:44.650 --> 34:45.816
Define my character
by firing candace?

34:45.818 --> 34:47.551
It's called
making a tough choice.

34:47.553 --> 34:48.852
A painful one.

34:48.854 --> 34:50.353
The right one.

34:50.355 --> 34:52.556
The voters will respect you

34:52.558 --> 34:54.157
For standing up
and doing the thing

34:54.159 --> 34:55.625
That no one wants
to ever have to do.

34:55.627 --> 34:56.693
And it's just
a matter of time

34:56.695 --> 34:58.562
Before
the u.S. Attorney's office

34:58.564 --> 35:00.664
Ties the burglary to candace.
Do it now!

35:00.666 --> 35:02.866
Come clean, and I can help you
move past this.

35:02.868 --> 35:04.434
If we wait for
the justice department

35:04.436 --> 35:06.136
To force your hand--
okay, understood.

35:09.807 --> 35:11.241
I'll prepare
a press conference,

35:11.243 --> 35:12.609
Help you work up
a statement.

35:12.611 --> 35:15.812
Figuring out what to tell
the press, I can handle.

35:15.814 --> 35:18.748
What I tell candace
is another story.

35:20.118 --> 35:21.585
(projector and camera shutter
clicks)

35:21.587 --> 35:23.787
This is where I spend
most of my time--

35:23.789 --> 35:25.388
My man cave, if you will.

35:25.390 --> 35:27.724
Sally decorated it
as a birthday present

35:27.726 --> 35:31.761
She claims it was to keep me
from being homesick.

35:31.763 --> 35:35.265
But mostly it was
to keep me out of her hair.

35:35.267 --> 35:37.300
My college lacrosse stuff.

35:37.302 --> 35:39.302
Apparently,
you were good.

35:39.304 --> 35:41.638
Won the s.E.L.C. Title
two years running.

35:41.640 --> 35:42.739
You keep in touch
with anyone?

35:42.741 --> 35:44.407
Not as much as I'd like.

35:44.409 --> 35:46.443
Back then, we were like
brothers to each other.

35:46.445 --> 35:48.712
All that time on the road,
the team building,

35:48.714 --> 35:51.848
It wasn't until after
I graduated college

35:51.850 --> 35:55.185
I realized how difficult
it is to form bonds

35:55.187 --> 35:56.486
That close out
in the real world.

35:56.488 --> 35:58.488
It's hard.

35:58.490 --> 36:00.257
Don't you agree?

36:00.259 --> 36:02.526
To make new friends
as a grown man.

36:02.528 --> 36:05.662
I-I was a theater major
at middlebury, so...

36:05.664 --> 36:07.831
I imagine it was
a very different experience

36:07.833 --> 36:09.399
Than playing a sport.

36:09.401 --> 36:10.867
Now, you and sally
met in college.

36:10.869 --> 36:12.235
Why don't you tell me
about that?

36:12.237 --> 36:13.570
I could.

36:13.572 --> 36:14.704
(sets down glass)
or we could just
cut to the chase

36:14.706 --> 36:16.339
And have a good time.

36:16.341 --> 36:18.208
(muffled) daniel!

36:18.210 --> 36:19.709
I'm sorry. Wait, stop.
What are you doing?

36:19.711 --> 36:20.777
You're not attracted
to me?

36:20.779 --> 36:22.512
You're married,
and I'm married.

36:22.514 --> 36:23.747
And I thought
you were straight!

36:23.749 --> 36:25.515
I guess I gave you
the wrong impression.

36:25.517 --> 36:26.716
Oh, my god. I-I-I...
Come on now...

36:26.718 --> 36:28.218
I need a minute!

36:28.220 --> 36:30.554
God. (exhales)

36:30.556 --> 36:33.190
Now wait a second!

36:33.192 --> 36:34.524
I...

36:36.861 --> 36:40.363
You can't go saying anything
about this to anybody.

36:40.365 --> 36:42.399
I never would've tried
anything if I hadn't heard

36:42.401 --> 36:43.733
That you were in
an open marriage.

36:43.735 --> 36:45.735
What? From who?!

36:45.737 --> 36:46.970
Mellie!

36:46.972 --> 36:49.272
She said you and cyrus
have some kind of...

36:49.274 --> 36:50.540
An arrangement.

36:50.542 --> 36:53.710
<i>On the vice president's</i>
<i>husband.</i>

36:53.712 --> 36:55.312
<i>They're looking</i>
<i>for a writer.</i>

36:55.314 --> 36:56.780
Next thing I know,

36:56.782 --> 36:58.782
You're suggesting that we do
this interview at the house

36:58.784 --> 37:00.417
On a night when you know
my wife is out of town.

37:00.419 --> 37:01.651
<i>Go to his place.</i>

37:01.653 --> 37:03.253
You come over here
with a bottle.

37:03.255 --> 37:04.588
<i>Bring over a bottle</i>
<i>of nice bourbon.</i>

37:04.590 --> 37:05.722
The hell am I supposed
to think?

37:05.724 --> 37:08.558
<i>He'll open right up.</i>

37:11.797 --> 37:16.866
It pains me to say
that the entire incident

37:16.868 --> 37:18.802
Was a shameful fraud...

37:18.804 --> 37:23.907
Entirely conceived
and executed by myself.

37:23.909 --> 37:26.843
(reporters shouting questions
at once)

37:26.845 --> 37:28.945
I staged the break-in

37:28.947 --> 37:32.282
And had the laptop planted
at reston headquarters.

37:32.284 --> 37:34.384
(under breath) no.
I wanna apologize

37:34.386 --> 37:36.987
To the reston campaign,
governor reston himself,

37:36.989 --> 37:39.522
And the american people
for this unforgivable

37:39.524 --> 37:41.691
Lapse in judgment on my part.

37:41.693 --> 37:44.561
As a result,
I am hereby announcing

37:44.563 --> 37:47.264
The withdrawal of my candidacy

37:47.266 --> 37:50.400
For the democratic
presidential nomination.

37:50.402 --> 37:54.437
My behavior clearly falls
beneath the standard

37:54.439 --> 37:56.339
For those who would aspire

37:56.341 --> 37:58.942
To the highest office
in the land.

37:58.944 --> 38:00.610
Thank you.

38:00.612 --> 38:02.045
And good-bye.

38:02.047 --> 38:03.647
You always said
I wasn't ready

38:03.649 --> 38:05.715
For a national race,
and you were right.

38:05.717 --> 38:08.051
You didn't have to do that.
We had options.

38:08.053 --> 38:09.719
Like throwing my own daughter
under the bus?

38:09.721 --> 38:11.588
What kind of mother
would do that? Would yours?

38:11.590 --> 38:14.557
With everything
I've already put her through

38:14.559 --> 38:15.992
With this campaign...

38:15.994 --> 38:17.360
She's just a kid.

38:17.362 --> 38:19.863
She'd never be able
to handle...

38:19.865 --> 38:21.665
I'll make the plea deal,

38:21.667 --> 38:24.567
Go back to montana,
if they'll still have me.

38:24.569 --> 38:27.637
See if I can maybe
make a difference there. So...

38:27.639 --> 38:29.072
Thanks for everything.

38:29.074 --> 38:31.308
You're welcome,
congresswoman.

38:36.414 --> 38:38.581
Don't, okay?
Just... Don't.

38:40.351 --> 38:41.418
(projector and camera shutter
clicking)

38:41.420 --> 38:43.453
(papers rustling)

38:43.455 --> 38:45.055
How was new hampshire?

38:45.057 --> 38:46.890
Good.

38:46.892 --> 38:49.359
Chilly, but good.

38:54.899 --> 38:57.600
Marcus dropped out
of the race.
I heard.

38:57.602 --> 39:00.437
Good for us.
We can beat reston again.

39:00.439 --> 39:02.005
We can.

39:03.908 --> 39:07.811
Means olivia's
available again.

39:07.813 --> 39:11.348
She might be a little more
amenable to the idea now.

39:14.118 --> 39:16.486
Maybe we should try again.

39:16.488 --> 39:19.956
Maybe we should.

39:19.958 --> 39:23.026
(otis redding's "try a little
tenderness" playing)

39:25.029 --> 39:29.566
¶

39:29.568 --> 39:31.067
(door opens)

39:33.471 --> 39:36.039
¶ oh, she may be weary

39:36.041 --> 39:42.112
¶ and young girls,
they do get weary ¶

39:42.114 --> 39:43.780
(door closes)
¶ wearing

39:43.782 --> 39:47.751
¶ that same old shaggy dress

39:47.753 --> 39:50.153
¶ yeah, yeah

39:50.155 --> 39:54.090
(sighs) hey, honey.
Hey.

39:54.092 --> 39:58.461
What?
Your interview.
It's almost midnight.

39:58.463 --> 39:59.929
I expected you back
a lot earlier.

39:59.931 --> 40:02.399
It turns out
you were right--

40:02.401 --> 40:03.933
Little booze...

40:03.935 --> 40:05.602
It opened him right up.

40:05.604 --> 40:08.405
Good. Glad to hear it.

40:08.407 --> 40:09.739
Thanks again.

40:09.741 --> 40:11.541
It feels good
to be back in the saddle.

40:11.543 --> 40:15.412
My pleasure.
You coming to bed?
Yeah.

40:15.414 --> 40:18.448
I'm just gonna...
Jump in the shower first.

40:18.450 --> 40:21.418
Long day. You don't have
to wait up.

40:21.420 --> 40:24.087
Okay.
Okay.

40:24.089 --> 40:27.791
¶ never, never, never possess

40:27.793 --> 40:28.992
Love you.

40:28.994 --> 40:31.494
Love you, too.

40:33.831 --> 40:36.065
(cell phone chimes and buzzes)

40:36.067 --> 40:37.700
(chimes and buzzes)

40:37.702 --> 40:41.171
¶ try a little tenderness

40:41.173 --> 40:44.541
¶

40:44.543 --> 40:48.445
¶ that's all you gotta do

40:48.447 --> 40:51.181
¶

40:51.183 --> 40:54.050
¶ it's not

40:54.052 --> 40:56.553
¶ just sentimental

40:56.555 --> 41:01.124
¶ no, no, no

41:01.126 --> 41:03.159
(sobs)
¶ she has

41:03.161 --> 41:07.597
(monitor beeping steadily)
what are you giving me?

41:07.599 --> 41:09.632
Just something
that'll send you off into

41:09.634 --> 41:12.735
A nice, long slumber.

41:12.737 --> 41:16.573
¶ they are spoke so gentle,
yeah ¶

41:19.944 --> 41:22.912
¶ it makes it easier

41:22.914 --> 41:27.150
¶ easier to bear

41:27.152 --> 41:28.251
¶ yeah

41:28.253 --> 41:32.655
¶ you won't regret it,
no, no ¶

41:32.657 --> 41:37.060
¶ some girls
they don't forget it ¶

41:37.062 --> 41:39.929
¶ love is their only

41:39.931 --> 41:42.665
¶ happiness, yeah

41:42.667 --> 41:43.833
(rowan) guard?!

41:48.172 --> 41:52.208
¶ but it's all so easy

41:52.210 --> 41:54.577
¶ all you gotta do is try

41:54.579 --> 41:58.248
¶ try a little tenderness

41:58.250 --> 42:00.617
